column2: TELL ME AN EMILY DICKINSON POEM

column5:
#Newline Emily Dickinson#Newline #Newline #Newline


  • My life closed twice before its close;#Newline
    It yet remains to see#Newline
    If Immortality unveil#Newline
    A third event to me#Comma#Newline
    So huge#Comma so hopeless to conceive#Comma#Newline
    As these that twice befell.#Newline
    Parting is all we know of heaven#Comma#Newline
    And all we need of hell.
    • #Newline


  • "Hope" is the thing with feathers
    #NewlineThat perches in the soul
    #NewlineAnd sings the tune without the words
    #NewlineAnd never stops at all.
    #Newline
    • #Newline


  • The brain is wider than the sky#Comma#Newline
    For#Comma put them side by side#Comma#Newline
    The one the other will contain#Newline
    With ease#Comma and you beside.#Newline
    • #Newline
